<section id="h11001">
<title>
<emphasis id="Preface" effect="bold">

Preface

</emphasis>


</title>




<para id="p1000">
This module is one in a collection of modules designed to help beginners 
	of all ages 

<emphasis id="em1000" effect="italics">
(8 and up)

</emphasis>
 learn how to create the code for computer 
	programs. Information is provided not only for the beginners themselves but 
	also for their parents and teachers where appropriate.

</para>




<para id="p1001">
The purpose of this module is to teach you how to write a Scratch program that uses the following relational operators: 


<emphasis id="em1001" effect="italics">
<emphasis id="strong1000" effect="bold">
less than

</emphasis>
, 

<emphasis id="strong1001" effect="bold">
equal to

</emphasis>
, 

</emphasis>
and

<emphasis id="em1002" effect="italics">
 

<emphasis id="strong1002" effect="bold">

greater than

</emphasis>
</emphasis>
.

</para>




